@edsantiago I tried but i was unable to reproduce this flake and I saw this rare occurrence once more when I was vendoring in `c/storage`. But running this test `podman parallel build should not race` on local never fails for me.

I tried running test multiple times as well using loop with build count also increased to `100` here : https://github.com/containers/podman/blob/main/test/system/070-build.bats#L222
```bash
for ((n=0;n<100;n++))
do
 if timeout -v 1 true; then PODMAN=$PWD/bin/podman bats test/system/ --filter "parallel"; else echo "Skipping $@: 'timeout -v' unavailable'"; fi
done
``` 

My output for 100 tests it never failed: https://0bin.net/paste/NZ5qSgBA#jX42T69r+MYH2geDlsRjzb6rltUevMJp81lfxoTa7a+

@edsantiago Could it be some other test which overlaps and cause this rare flake (but I doubt ) ?  Cause running this test in isolated manner never fails for me. I am running only following test on my local `podman parallel build should not race` with other tests disabled.

/approve
LGTM
